<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="551" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,582,1149]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">
Of the three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1923" box="[442,610,619,645]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Paracypridinae">Paracypridinae</taxonomicName>
found during our study (
<taxonomicName authority="Okubo, 1980" authorityName="Okubo" authorityYear="1980" box="[923,1429,619,645]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Dolerocypria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mukaishimensis">
<emphasis box="[923,1263,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">Dolerocypria mukaishimensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Okubo, I." box="[1277,1429,619,645]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="18 - 27" refId="ref14518" refString="Okubo, I. (1980) Three new species of the family Candonidae (Ostracoda) from the Inland Sea of Japan. Proceedings of the Japanese Society of Systematic Zoology, 18, 18 - 27." type="journal article" year="1980">Okubo, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith &amp; Kamiya, 2006" authorityName="Smith &amp; Kamiya" authorityYear="2006" box="[151,630,655,681]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Paracypria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adnata">
<emphasis box="[151,363,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">Paracypria adnata</emphasis>
Smith &amp; Kamiya, 2006
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Okubo, 1980))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Okubo" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[684,1130,655,681]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Paracypria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inujimensis">
<emphasis box="[684,946,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">Paracypria inujimensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Okubo, I." box="[960,1111,655,681]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="18 - 27" refId="ref14518" refString="Okubo, I. (1980) Three new species of the family Candonidae (Ostracoda) from the Inland Sea of Japan. Proceedings of the Japanese Society of Systematic Zoology, 18, 18 - 27." type="journal article" year="1980">Okubo, 1980</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
, all have a small protrusion on the antero-ventral calcified inner lamella of the left valve (
<figureCitation box="[840,1018,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[215,1373,181,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[215,1373,181,1693]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. A &amp; B, Cryptocandona tsukagoshii. A, female, RV, ext. B, female, LV, int. C &amp; D, Fabaeformiscandona subacuta. C, male, LV, ext. D, male, RV, int. E &amp; F, Pseudocandona abei. E, female, LV, ext. F, female, LV, int. G &amp; H, Schellencandona yakushimaensis. G, female, LV, ext. H, female RV, int. I &amp; J, Physocypria nipponica. I, male, RV, ext. J, male, LV, int. K &amp; L, Cypretta seurati. K, female, RV, ext. L, female, RV int. M–O, Dolerocypria mukaishimensis. M, male, RV, ext. N, male, LV, int., arrow indicates position of antero-ventral tooth. O, male, LV, int., detail of antero-ventral tooth. P–R, Paracypria adnata. P, male, RV, ext. Q, male, LV, int., arrow indicates position of antero-ventral tooth. R, male, LV, int., detail of antero-ventral tooth. S–U, Paracypria inujimensis. S, female, RV, ext. T, female, LV, int., arrow indicates position of antero-ventral tooth. U, female, LV, int., detail of antero-ventral tooth. Scale bar = 445 µm for A &amp; B, 617 µm for C &amp; D, 381 µm for E &amp; F, 289 µm for G &amp; H, 403 µm for I &amp; J, 464 µm for K &amp; L, 396 µm for M &amp; N, 392 µm for P &amp; Q, 473 µm for S &amp; T, and 77 µm for O, R &amp; U." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626925" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626925/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">Fig. 8O, R &amp; U</figureCitation>
), a feature that has not been recorded in these species before. Within the tribe, the 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartmann &amp; Puri, 1974" authorityName="Hartmann &amp; Puri" authorityYear="1974" box="[653,1131,727,753]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Thalassocypridini">
Thalassocypridini 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann, G. &amp; Puri, H. S." box="[862,1131,727,753]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="7 - 73" refId="ref13060" refString="Hartmann, G. &amp; Puri, H. S. (1974) Summary of neontological and paleontological classification of Ostracoda. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 70, 7 - 73." type="journal article" year="1974">Hartmann &amp; Puri, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, some species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Harding, 1962" authorityName="Harding" authorityYear="1962" box="[151,425,763,789]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Mungava" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,257,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">Mungava</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Harding, J. P." box="[263,425,763,789]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="51 - 62" refId="ref12872" refString="Harding, J. P. (1962) Mungava munda and four other new species of ostracod crustaceans from fish stomachs. The Natural History of Rennell Island, British Solomon Islands, 4, 51 - 62." type="journal article" year="1962">Harding, 1962</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have similar small protrusions on the left valve (the antero-ventral knob-like thickening of 
<bibRefCitation author="Wouters, K." box="[151,311,799,825]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="171 - 184" refId="ref16205" refString="Wouters, K. (1987) The genus Mungava Harding, 1962 (Crustacea: Ostracoda) from Indo-Pacific brackish waters, with the description of two new species. Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Biologie, 57, 171 - 184." type="journal article" year="1987">Wouters 1987</bibRefCitation>
), but it is absent in others (
<bibRefCitation author="Maddocks, R. F." box="[616,803,798,825]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="169 - 216" refId="ref13926" refString="Maddocks, R. F. (2005) New thalassocypridine Ostracoda from anchialine caves of the Loyalty Islands, New Caledonia (Podocopida, Paracypridinae). Micropaleontology, 51 (3), 169 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.2113 / 51.3.169" type="journal article" year="2005">Maddocks 2005</bibRefCitation>
). A similar protrusion also appears present in both 
<taxonomicName authority="Hiruta &amp; Kakui, 2016" authorityName="Hiruta &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2016" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Mangalocypria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">Mangalocypria ryukyuensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hiruta, S. F. &amp; Kakui, K." box="[419,666,835,861]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="515 - 539" refId="ref13218" refString="Hiruta, S. F. &amp; Kakui, K. (2016) Three new brackish-water thalassocypridine species (Crustacea: Ostracoda: Paracyprididae) from the Ryukyu Islands, southwestern Japan. Zootaxa, 4169 (3), 515 - 539. http: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4169.3.6" type="journal article" year="2016">Hiruta &amp; Kakui, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hiruta &amp; Kakui, 2016" authorityName="Hiruta &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2016" box="[721,1205,835,861]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Paracypria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumosa">
<emphasis box="[721,951,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">Paracypria plumosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hiruta, S. F. &amp; Kakui, K." box="[958,1205,835,861]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="515 - 539" refId="ref13218" refString="Hiruta, S. F. &amp; Kakui, K. (2016) Three new brackish-water thalassocypridine species (Crustacea: Ostracoda: Paracyprididae) from the Ryukyu Islands, southwestern Japan. Zootaxa, 4169 (3), 515 - 539. http: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4169.3.6" type="journal article" year="2016">Hiruta &amp; Kakui, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see SEM figures in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hiruta, S. F. &amp; Kakui, K." box="[151,396,871,898]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="515 - 539" refId="ref13218" refString="Hiruta, S. F. &amp; Kakui, K. (2016) Three new brackish-water thalassocypridine species (Crustacea: Ostracoda: Paracyprididae) from the Ryukyu Islands, southwestern Japan. Zootaxa, 4169 (3), 515 - 539. http: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4169.3.6" type="journal article" year="2016">Hiruta &amp; Kakui 2016</bibRefCitation>
), but due to a lack of internal SEM photographs of the left valve for most 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartmann &amp; Puri" authorityYear="1974" box="[1236,1437,871,897]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Thalassocypridini">Thalassocypridini</taxonomicName>
species, it is not clear how widespread this feature is. A tooth on the antero-ventral calcified inner lamella of the left valve and a corresponding socket on the right valve were used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wouters, K." box="[881,1055,943,969]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="101 - 112" refId="ref16254" refString="Wouters, K. (2001) On the genera Dolerocypria and Hansacypris (Crustacea, Ostracoda), with the description of three new species from Papua New Guinea. Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Biologie, 71, 101 - 112." type="journal article" year="2001">Wouters (2001)</bibRefCitation>
as a diagnostic feature of the tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="McKenzie, 1980" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1980" box="[151,535,979,1005]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Renaudcypridini">
Renaudcypridini 
<bibRefCitation author="McKenzie, K. G." box="[345,535,979,1005]" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" pagination="507 - 515" refId="ref14128" refString="McKenzie, K. G. (1980) A new subfamily from Gorong, Seram, Moluccas, with the description of Renaudcypris new genus (Crustacea, Ostracoda). Bulletin du Museum national d'histoire naturelle, 2, 507 - 515." type="journal article" year="1980">McKenzie, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. There is no corresponding socket on the right valve in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith &amp; Kamiya" authorityYear="2006" box="[1161,1267,979,1005]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Paracypria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adnata">
<emphasis box="[1161,1267,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">P. adnata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Okubo" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[1281,1437,979,1004]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Paracypria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inujimensis">
<emphasis box="[1281,1437,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">P. inujimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[197,415,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="551">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okubo" authorityYear="1980" box="[197,410,1015,1041]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Dolerocypria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mukaishimensis">D. mukaishimensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and it seems that instead the edge of the right valve clips into the gap between the protrusion and the edge of the left valve. However, the protrusion in these three species is probably homologous with the tooth of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1980" box="[227,417,1087,1113]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Renaudcypridini">Renaudcypridini</taxonomicName>
. Although the protrusion/tooth/knob is present in at least some of the species in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartmann &amp; Puri" authorityYear="1974" box="[151,355,1123,1149]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Thalassocypridini">Thalassocypridini</taxonomicName>
, a socket on the right valve may still be a diagnostic feature of the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1980" box="[1161,1351,1123,1149]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="22" pageNumber="551" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Renaudcypridini">Renaudcypridini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
